  <title translate="true">Introduction</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Online Guide to MODFLOW</text><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2000"/><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">-2000</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2005"/><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">-2005</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-LGR"/><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">-LGR</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-CFP"/><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">-CFP</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-NWT"/><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">-NWT</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-FMP2"/><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><link displaytype="image" src="water_banner1.png" type="weblink" href="http://www.usgs.gov/" target="_blank"><title translate="true">USGS Home Page</title></link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Compiled by </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="weblink" href="mailto:rbwinst@usgs.gov" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Richard B. Winston</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Revised: </text><var styleclass="Normal">&lt;%DATE%&gt;</var></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Introduction</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The purpose of </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="HTML"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">these web pages</text><conditional-text type="ELSE"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">this help file</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is to provide a unified description of the formats for </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2000"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000,</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2005"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-2005</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-LGR"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-LGR</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-CFP"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-CFP</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-NWT"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-NWT</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-FMP2"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="ALLMODELS"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-2000, MODFLOW-2005, MODFLOW-LGR, MODFLOW-CFP, MODFLOW-NWT, and MODFLOW-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> input files. &#160;These descriptions have been copied from the original reports in which they were published and supplemented with materials found in the &quot;doc&quot; directory of the </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2000"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2005"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-2005</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-LGR"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-LGR</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-CFP"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-CFP</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-NWT"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-NWT</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-FMP2"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="ALLMODELS"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000, MODFLOW-2005, MODFLOW-LGR &#160;MODFLOW-CFP, MODFLOW-NWT, and MODFLOW-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> distribution file</text><conditional-text type="IF" value="ALLMODELS"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">s</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. &#160;</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">These web pages are not substitute for or a definitive guide to </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2000"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2005"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true"> MODFLOW-2005</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-LGR"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true"> MODFLOW-LGR</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-CFP"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">MODFLOW-CFP</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-NWT"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">MODFLOW-NWT</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-FMP2"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">MODFLOW-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="ALLMODELS"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000, MODFLOW-2005, MODFLOW-LGR, MODFLOW-CFP</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, MODFLOW-NWT, and MODFLOW-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">. &#160;They may contain errors that are not in the original documents. &#160;In case of doubt, consult the original documents or examine the source code.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In a few cases, obvious typographical errors in the original documents have been corrected in the version of the input instructions presented on these web pages. &#160;Such changes are not marked. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Some packages, such as the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="IBS" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Interbed Storage</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> package, were originally published as part of MODFLOW-88. &#160;In such cases, the instructions for including these package in a </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2000"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2005"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-2005</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-LGR"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-LGR</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-CFP"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-CFP</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-NWT"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-NWT</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="ALLMODELS"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000, MODFLOW-2005, MODFLOW-LGR, MODFLOW-CFP, MODFLOW-OWHM, or MODFLOW-NWT</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> model have been updated to reflect how the input is specified in </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2000"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2005"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-2005</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-LGR"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> MODFLOW-LGR</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-CFP"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-CFP</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-NWT"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-NWT</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-FMP2"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="ALLMODELS"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000, MODFLOW-2005, MODFLOW-LGR, MODFLOW-CFP, MODFLOW-NWT, and MODFLOW-OWHM</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">In a few cases, the instructions have been supplemented by additional material not found in the original input instructions. &#160;Such materials are shown in a different type face like </text><text styleclass="New Materials" translate="true">this</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. &#160;The sources of such additional material include examination of the source code, correspondence with the authors of a package, and experience. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Keywords in the input files that must be entered exactly as shown (in a case-insensitive manner) are displayed in these web pages in bold and italics like </text><text styleclass="Keywords" translate="true">this</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Please send comments and corrections to Richard B. Winston (</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="weblink" href="mailto:rbwinst@usgs.gov" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">rbwinst@usgs.gov</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">).</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">This guide reflects </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2000"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000 version 1.19.01</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-2005"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW-2005 version 1.11.00</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-LGR"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW-LGR versions 1.2 and 2.0</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-CFP"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW-CFP version 1.8.00</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-NWT"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW-NWT version 1.0.8</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="MODFLOW-FMP2"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW-OWHM version 1.0.00</text><conditional-text type="END"/><conditional-text type="IF" value="ALLMODELS"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW-2000 version 1.19.01, MODFLOW-2005 version 1.11.00, MODFLOW-LGR version 1.2 and 2.0, MODFLOW-CFP version 1.8.00, MODFLOW-NWT version 1.0.8, and MODFLOW-OWHM version 1.0.00</text><conditional-text type="END"/><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Guides to other versions of MODFLOW can be found at the following locations</text><conditional-text type="IFNOT" value="MODFLOW-2000"/></para>
